## 🎛️ Detailed Control & Operations Manual

Using the interactive workspace dashboard is highly intuitive and requires zero development knowledge:

* **Setting Up Income:** Type your primary net revenue in the `Monthly Income ($)` parameter box. The plant calculates structural growth metrics exclusively relative to this core integer figure.
* **Adding Specific Categories:** Click the green `+ Add Category` button. The JavaScript execution engine instantly creates a structural row wrapper containing an empty item description box, an independent number value container, and a deletion trigger.
* **Removing Individual Expenses:** Click the red `×` button flanking any individual category field row. The application instantly detaches that element node from the layout matrix, subtracts its cost footprint from the current global register, saves the new clean dataset, and animates the plant downward smoothly.
* **Wiping System Memory:** Click the grey `Clear All` button. A fallback safety modal validation prompt asks if you want to execute the system cache reset. Confirming this instantly vaporizes the local storage record file, clears out screen data layouts, and sets the system state back to its baseline placeholder properties.
* **Exporting Text Documents:** Click the blue `Download Report` button. The script calculates your ledger totals in the background and saves a file named `cozy-budget-report.txt` onto your computer.

