## 🚀 Deployment & Installation Checklist

Because this web app runs on raw client-side technologies without server dependencies, hosting your application live to the web via GitHub Pages is simple and free:

1. **Upload Files:** Drag, drop, and commit your `index.html` and `script.js` files into your public repository.
2. **Access Project Settings:** Click the **Settings** (gear icon) tab located in the repository navigation strip.
3. **Navigate to GitHub Pages:** Locate the **Pages** menu link on the lower left-hand navigation column list.
4. **Select Source Branch:** Look under the *Build and Deployment* workspace dashboard. Switch the Branch selection filter from **None** over to **main** (or **master**).
5. **Publish Code Live:** Leave the folder root field set to `/(root)` and select **Save**. Your permanent web tracking platform URL link will compile live within sixty seconds!
